title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Find the distribution of customers based on how many orders they have placed. Include customers with zero orders. Ignore any orders whose comment contains the substring ‘special’ followed by ‘requests’. Count how many customers fall into each order-count group and output the number of customers per group. Sort by most orders. Output in textfile.

operations.table: (SELECT o_orderkey, o_custkey, o_comment FROM orders) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val c = r.getField(2).toString; c.contains("special") && c.contains("requests") }
(a: (Int, Int), b: (Int, Int)) => if (a._2 >= b._2) a else b

log.thoughts: Plan computes the distribution of customers with at least one order by counting orders per customer (ignoring orders whose comments contain the substring 'special' and 'requests'), then aggregates counts per distinct order count. The final results are emitted to a text file, sorted by the number of orders in descending order.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT c_custkey FROM (SELECT c_custkey FROM customer) as X) as X
(SELECT o_orderkey, o_custkey, o_comment FROM (SELECT o_orderkey, o_custkey, o_comment FROM orders) as X) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val c = r.getField(2).toString; c.contains("special") && c.contains("requests") }
(a: (Int, Int), b: (Int, Int)) => if (a._2 >= b._2) a else b
